Download 6 months of food tracking data from my fitness pal into an excel file for further analysis.
Here are the steps I followed:

Step 1: Open MyFitnessPal app and navigate to the "Progress" section

Step 2: Tap on the 3 horizontal lines in the upper left corner to open the menu and select "Advanced Settings"

Step 3: Scroll down to the "Data Management" section and tap on "Export Diary Data"

Step 4: Select the date range you want to export (In this case, I selected 6 months) 

Step 5: Choose the format as CSV (which is compatible with Excel)

Step 6: Wait for the export process to complete (this may take a few minutes depending on the amount of data)

Step 7: Once the export is complete, you'll receive an email with a download link for the CSV file.

(defun parse-sg-rss-xml (rss-string)
  (let ((temp-lst nil))
    (when (not *sg-rules*) 
      (setup-rules))
    (funcall 'add-sgml-parse-region 'Parse-SG-RSS temp-lst) 
    (funcall 'Parse-SG-RSS v rss-string)))

  (push `(("<item([^]*)>"

                     NIL)))
            *sg-rules*)
  (push `(,( lambda (attr-name content-parser-fun)

         *sg-rules*)

)
